OL,3,CPolice and probation service 'failed'
OL,4,Cmurdered father of one
OL,6,FThe fact that McGlacken had committed
OL,7,Fa crime - in breach of his licence -
OL,8,Fwas also then not passed on to the
OL,9,FProbation Service, who were
OL,10,Fsupervising him while on licence.
OL,12,FThe court heard how McGlacken and
OL,13,FEvitt were both under the supervision
OL,14,Fof the Greater Manchester region of
OL,15,Fthe Probation Service at the time of
OL,16,FAshley's death, having both recently
OL,17,Fbeen released from prison after being
OL,18,Fsentenced as co-defendants to an
OL,19,Fattempted burglary.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/16
