OL,4,Cmurdered father of one
OL,6,FAshley's family feel his death could
OL,7,Fhave been avoided, and have insisted
OL,8,Fthey were let down by the police and
OL,9,Fprobation service.
OL,11,F"We say the men who took Ashley from
OL,12,Fus should not have been in a position
OL,13,Fto commit this horrific crime,"
OL,14,FBenjamin Burrows, of Leigh Day
OL,15,FSolicitors, speaking on behalf of the
OL,16,Ffamily said.
OL,18,F"Both the police and probation had
OL,19,Fcritical information but didn't act on
OL,20,Fit and opportunities to protect Ashley
OL,21,Fwere missed.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/16
