OL,3,CPolice and probation service 'failed'
OL,4,Cmurdered father of one
OL,6,FAn officer was sent to McGlacken's
OL,7,Fproperty - not to charge him with an
OL,8,Foffence - but to educate him through a
OL,9,Fpolicing process known as 'restorative
OL,10,Fjustice' or 'community resolution'.
OL,12,FHe had first discussed the visit with
OL,13,Fa more experienced colleague, but the
OL,14,Fdecision was made with both officers
OL,15,Funaware of McGlacken's previous
OL,16,Fconvictions, or the fact he was on
OL,17,Flicence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/16
