OL,3,CPolice and probation service 'failed'
OL,4,Cmurdered father of one
OL,6,FCoroner Golombek heard evidence in
OL,7,Frelation to GMP's visit to McGlacken's
OL,8,Fhome, and in relation to the Probation
OL,9,FService's supervision of McGlacken and
OL,10,Fof Evitt, who was also on licence from
OL,11,Fprison at the time of the murder.
OL,13,FRecording a short form conclusion of
OL,14,Funlawful killing, Mr Golombek said
OL,15,Fthere were failures by GMP and the
OL,16,FProbation Service. He said GMP had
OL,17,F"ample opportunity" to discover
OL,18,FMcGlacken was on licence, and that
OL,19,Fthere were "failings" in the
OL,20,Fmanagement of both McGlacken and Evitt
OL,21,Ffrom the Probation Service.
