OL,6,FAshley's family feel his death could
OL,7,Fhave been avoided had GMP passed on
OL,8,Finformation about McGlacken's breach
OL,9,Fof licence to the probation service on
OL,10,F6 December 2021, and had the probation
OL,11,Fservice taken steps to properly manage
OL,12,Fthe risk of serious harm posed by
OL,13,FMcGlacken and Evitt following their
OL,14,Frelease from prison.
OL,16,FIn a statement they said: "We are
OL,17,Fdevastated beyond words by the loss of
OL,18,FAshley. He was a loving son, brother,
OL,19,Fgrandson, father, nephew, and friend
OL,20,Fwhose life was brutally taken in an
OL,21,Fact of violence.
